        <div class="question">


            <div class="welovestackoverflow" style="margin-top: 10px;">
                <div style="float: left;">
                        <p>
Modular arithmetic (clock arithmetic) is a system of integer arithmetic based on the congruence relation $a \equiv b \pmod{n}$ which means that $n$ divides $b-a$.                         </p>
                                            <p style="margin-bottom: 0;">
                            <a title="tag wiki" href="/tags/modular-arithmetic/info">learn more&hellip;</a>
                            <span class="lsep">|</span> 
                            <a title="top answerers and askers in this tag" href="/tags/modular-arithmetic/topusers">top users</a> 
                            <span class="lsep">|</span> 
                            <a title="common, alternate spellings or phrasings for this tag" href="/tags/modular-arithmetic/synonyms">synonyms</a>
                                                    </p>
                </div>
