    <div class="summary">        
        <h3><a href="/questions/532772/if-gcd-a-m-c-then-axc-mod-m-has-d-gcd-a-m-many-solutions" class="question-hyperlink">if gcd (a,m) = c, then ax≡c (mod m) has d = gcd (a,m) many solutions</a></h3>
        <div class="excerpt">
            The theorem is

ax≡c (mod m) is solvable if and only if gcd (a,m)|c

and if gcd (a,m) = c, then ax≡c (mod m) has d = gcd (a,m) many solutions that are pairwise not congruent to one another (mod m)

...
        </div>
             
